<item>
            <title>[SOLR-13058] Probable synchronization bug in OverseerTaskProcessor</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-13058</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hit this stack trace:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
solr/beast-results/TimeRoutedAliasUpdateProcessorTest/1/683/stdout- [junit4] &amp;gt; Throwable #1: com.carrotsearch.randomizedtesting.UncaughtExceptionError: Captured an uncaught exception in thread: &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Thread&lt;/span&gt;[id=746, name=OverseerThreadFactory-164-thread-4, state=RUNNABLE, group=Overseer collection creation process.]
